word_mean_info__list.difference: 指提供某种服务收取的固定费用。
多指通过劳动或投资等手段所得到的收入。
多用复数形式，指按小时、日或星期的报酬，通常指体力劳动者的工资。
与earnings含义很相近，但前者强调总收入。
指按年定下，按月或星期平均给予的报酬，指脑力劳动者的薪水。
主要指个人收入，包括劳动所得和利润。
专指国家或企业的收入，主要指国家的税收。

bilingual.source: We should all try to be the sort of person who maintains a balance between their income and expenses well.
bilingual.target: 我们都应该努力成为那种能很好地平衡收入和支出的人。

bilingual.source: His income accounts for one-third of the family's total income.
bilingual.target: 他的收入占比例了家庭总收入的三分之一。

bilingual.source: Income redistribution can help low-income families improve their living conditions.
bilingual.target: 收入再分配可以帮助低收入家庭改善生活条件。
她的收入在一年内加倍了。

bilingual.source: She relies solely on her own income.
bilingual.target: 她仅仅依靠自己的收入。

yingyinNormal.en: My expenses account for 46.9% of my after-tax income.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的日常开支占我税后收入的46.9%。

yingyinNormal.en: Money's a sensitive subject for Howie, because of the difference in our income.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我们收入有差距，所以华仔对钱这个话题很敏感。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm talking rock-bottom FICO scores. No income verification. Adjustable rates. Dog shit!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我指的是信贷评分的最低分，无需收入证明，浮动利率，狗屁！

yingyinNormal.en: Even if they have no money? Well, my firm offers NINJA loans. "No Income, No Job."
yingyinNormal.zh: 即使他们没钱也没问题？我的公司提供"忍者"贷款，"没收入，没工作"。

yingyinNormal.en: We took action to offer millions of students a chance to cap their student loan payments at 10% of their income.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们还采取措施确保大学生每月的贷款还款额不超过其收入的10%，这将惠及数百万学子。

yingyinNormal.en: I just leave the income section blank if I want. Corporate doesn't care. These people just want homes. You know, and they go with the flow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我把收入那一栏空着就好了，公司不介意这个的，这些人就想有个住的地方，就顺其自然了。

yingyinNormal.en: In order to do that, it's time to have a fair tax structure one that values paychecks as much as unearned income and inherited wealth, to take some of the burden off of the middle class.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了达到这一目标，我们应该改革税收体制，把非工资收入和继承遗产都作为个人所得进行征税，减轻中产阶级税收负担。

yingyinNormal.en: It would be nice to have the increased income. Stop taking money from my parents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 终身教职的薪水会更高，这样就可以不用管爸妈要钱了。

yingyinNormal.en: And if you don't have a new friend by 9:00 tomorrow, as natural as flowers in the springtime, well, then maybe Leonard, the income tax attorney in Mommy's office, he's gonna do just a little bit of research into their family's paperwork and see if there're any inconsistencies.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接着如果明天早上九点之前你还不能像春暖花开那样自然而然地有一个新朋友，那么妈妈办公室里的所得税律师，伦纳德，就会对他们家的相关文件做一些小调查，看看有没有什么前后矛盾的地。

examination_example.sentence: Lower-<highlight>income</highlight> jobs like gardening or day care don't appeal to robots.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 像园艺或日托这样的低收入工作对机器人没有吸引力。

examination_example.sentence: Worse, the crucial <highlight>income</highlight> to feed yourself and your family and pay the bills has disappeared.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 更糟糕的是，养活自己和家人以及支付账单的关键收入已经消失了。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Income</highlight> inequality usually falls during a recession, but it has not shrunk in this one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 收入不平等的现象通常会在衰退期间减少，但在这次衰退中并没有缩小。

sense_info_list.en: money received, especially on a regular basis, for work or through investments

examination_example.sentence: Data reveals that economic inequality rather than family <highlight>income</highlight> might affect people's wellbeing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 数据显示，影响人们福祉的可能是经济不平等，而不是家庭收入。

examination_example.sentence: Commentators seized on the recent report by the Census Bureau, which found that average household <highlight>income</highlight> rose by 5.2% in 2015.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 评论员们关注了美国人口普查局(Census Bureau)的最新报告，这份报告显示，2015年美国家庭平均收入增长了5.2%。

examination_example.sentence: Even if precisely measured, <highlight>income</highlight> data exclude important determinants of economic well-being, such as the hours of work needed to earn that <highlight>income</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使经过精确计量，收入数据也不包括经济福利这种重要的决定因素，例如赚取该收入所需的工作时间。

examination_example.sentence: While by no means perfect, it is considerably more comprehensive than average <highlight>income</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管这绝非完美，但它比只考虑平均收入要全面得多。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 多指通过劳动或投资等手段所得到的收入。

sense_info_list.en: money received, especially on a regular basis, for work or through investments

examination_example.sentence: Rubber trees, the local people’s main source of <highlight>income</highlight> (收入来源), were so dry that they could no longer produce rubber latex (橡胶乳).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 橡胶树是当地人的主要收入来源，由于太干燥，他们再也不能生产橡胶胶乳了。

examination_example.sentence: The per capital <highlight>income</highlight> (人均收入) reached 12, 670 yuan, 40 times more than in the 1990s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人均收入达到12670元，比上世纪90年代增长了40倍。

examination_example.sentence: In 2020, its <highlight>income</highlight>  (收入) reached over 10 billion dollars, an increase of 100 percent over the year before.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2020年，其收入超过100亿美元，比前一年增长了100%。
